doc.previous: Cambridge University Press is both the oldest publishing house in the world and the oldest university press It originated from Letters Patent similar to a royal charter granted to the University of Cambridge by Henry VIII in 1534 and has been producing books continuously since the first University Press book was printed Cambridge is one of the two privileged presses the other being Oxford University Press Authors published by Cambridge have included John Milton William Harvey Isaac Newton Bertrand Russell and Stephen Hawking 4
doc.after: University printing began in Cambridge when the first practising University Printer Thomas Thomas set up a printing house on the site of what became the Senate House lawn a few yards from where the Press s bookshop now stands In those days the Stationers Company in London jealously guarded its monopoly of printing which partly explains the delay between the date of the University s Letters Patent and the printing of the first book
